WHAT IS SAUTOCONF?

sautoconf is a set of m4 macros to be used with autoconf in order to make it *s*impler to use with a nicer configure output. In particular it proposes the concept of feature to handle optional feature properly.


HOW TO USE IT

Create a simlink from sautoconf.m4 to acinclude.m4 in tour autoconf managed directory.See the test/ directory for some samples.


Please report any errors, updates, or suggestions to serge.guelton@telecom-bretagne.eu.
